				\begin{document}$$PD=\frac{{2[}^{30}{N}_{2}]}{dt\times [S]}$$\end{document}where [30N2] is the concentration of 15N-labelled N2 gas at the end of the incubation (µM), dt is the incubation time (d), and [S] is the concentration of the slurry (cm3 of fresh sediment L−1). We assumed that at the beginning of the incubation concentrations of 15N-labelled N2 were negligible.
